ety of diverse contexts in Africa and Europe, this book surveys key experiences and summarises lessons learned from the Mistra Urban Futures' global research platforms. It demonstrates best practice for developing and deploying different forms of transdisciplinary co-production, covering topics including neighbourhood transformation and housing justice, sustainable urban and transport development, urban food security and cultural heritage.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / City Planning & Urban Development.2bisacsh1 aBjörling, Nils, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCroese, Sylvia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDiprose, Kristina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDurakovic, Elma, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDymitrow, Mirek, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaysom, Gareth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIngelhag, Karin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJernsand, Eva Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohansson, Magnus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKotze, Shelley, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKraff, Helena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNess, Barry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNordqvist, Joakim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOloko, 